reviews.text: A small western restaurant next to a home decoration shop as it is part of the shop.  Nice dining environment and nice service too.  It has Impossible Burger listed in the regular menu.  Alternatively, I requested for another vegan main dish came with pumpkin soup.  The pasta like fettuccine but thicker, the texture was good.  The beetroot flakes should be air dried or baked.  It's not crispy or soft.  Pumpkin soup was not thick in texture as I had elsewhere, I think it was mixed with carrot and so that it was not stodgy.  However, pumpkin did not give strong flavour to the soup, if you love pumpkin, you are not satisfied with the soup.
A lovely place for lunch, special salad, yummy dishes that making me keep going back, nice place and people.. anyone who have been there, would love to go back!

I experienced terrible customer service and attitude from your cashier today. When I asked if I could sit outside he insisted that it was wet and at my own risk. Please note it wasn't raining and all that was required was for someone to wipe down the table. He continued to give me attitude and said that you didn't have a licence to serve outside. I am sorry if you don't have a licence why do you have tables!? Just another excuse of a lazy person with poor customer service!

 I really want impressed at all!

The food is defo over-priced. The tastier thing in this two dishes were the sweet potato fried. And i guess the patty melt was fine too. For the noodles, it’s served at room temperature(?) and it only looked good but didnt taste good. The scallops were fine.
If u want to chill, this may be a place for you, with its rather open outdoor area. But just dont expect too much for the food.
Lovely salad and coffee. There is an outdoor area which is great for cooler days.
